'''Calais''' is a service by [[Thomson Reuters]] that automatically extracts [[semantic]] information from web pages in a format that can be used on the [[semantic web]].<ref>[http://www.opencalais.com Calais Overview]</ref> Calais was launched in January 2008, and is free to use.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.readwriteweb.com/archives/reuters_calais.php# |title=Reuters Wants The World To Be Tagged |access-date=2008-04-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080411111826/http://www.readwriteweb.com/archives/reuters_calais.php# |archive-date=2008-04-11 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>[http://www.economist.com/displaystory.cfm?story_id=11002939 Start making sense]</ref>

The Calais [[Web service]] reads [[Unstructured data|unstructured]] text and returns [[Resource Description Framework]] formatted results identifying entities, facts and events within the text.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.opencalais.com/calaisAPI# |title=Calais API guide |access-date=2008-10-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081023021111/http://opencalais.com/calaisAPI# |archive-date=2008-10-23 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> The service appears to be based on technology acquired when Reuters purchased [[ClearForest]] in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|title=ClearForest|url=http://clearforest.com/|access-date=2012-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130124003538/http://clearforest.com/#|archive-date=2013-01-24|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> 

The technology has also been used to automatically [[tag (metadata)|tag]] [[blog]] articles<ref>[http://www.dangrossman.info/wp-calais-auto-tagger/ WP Calais Auto Tagger]</ref> and organize museum collections.<ref>[http://www.powerhousemuseum.com/dmsblog/index.php/2008/03/31/opac20-opencalais-meets-our-museum-collection-auto-tagging-and-semantic-parsing-of-collection-data/ OpenCalais meets our museum collection /auto-tagging and semantic parsing of collection data]</ref>

Calais uses [[natural language processing]] technologies delivered via a [[Web service|web service interface]].

