{{Infobox language |name = Nyindrou |nativename = |states = [[Papua New Guinea]] |region = westernmost [[Manus Island]], [[Manus Province]] |speakers = 4,200 |date=1998 |ref=e18 |familycolor = Austronesian |fam2 = [[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3 = [[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4 = [[Admiralty Islands languages|Admiralty Islands]] |fam5 = [[Eastern Admiralty Islands languages|Eastern Admiralty Islands]] |fam6 = [[Manus languages|Manus]] |fam7 = [[West Manus languages|West Manus]] |iso3 = lid |glotto=nyin1250 |glottorefname=Nyindrou }}
The '''Nyindrou language''' is a [[West Manus languages|West Manus language]] spoken by approximately 4200 people in the westernmost part of [[Manus Island]], [[Manus Province]] of [[Papua New Guinea]].<ref name=Ethnologue>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=lid Ethnologue report for Nyindrou]</ref> It has [[subject–verb–object|SVO word order]].<ref name=Ethnologue/>
